      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "1. Start by boiling a large pot of salted water and cook the spaghetti according to the package instructions until al dente.\n2. While the pasta is cooking, finely chop the garlic and mince the parsley.\n3. In a large pan, heat a generous amount of olive oil over medium heat and add the minced garlic, sautéing until fragrant and golden brown.\n4. Add the red chili flakes to the pan and stir well, allowing the flavors to meld together.\n5. Drain the cooked spaghetti and add it to the pan with the garlic and chili flakes, tossing to coat the pasta evenly.\n6. Sprinkle the chopped parsley over the pasta, tossing once more to distribute the fresh herbs.\n7. Serve the spicy garlic pasta immediately, garnishing with additional red chili flakes and parsley if desired.\n\nThis version maximizes the count of the main ingredients while maintaining readability.",
